* Update postMasterOracle.sql

1) Remove use of SUSPEND, which is dependent on seldom-used Oracle Resource Manager
2) Handle scenario with SQL*Plus connecting "/NOLOG" and database instance not OPEN successfully
3) Handle scenario with database instance running in NOARCHIVELOG mode successfully

* Update preOracleMaster.sql

1) remove use of SUSPEND, which is dependent on seldom-used Oracle Resource Manager
2) handle scenario where SQL*Plus is started with "/NOLOG" option and Oracle database instance is not OPEN
3) handle scenario where Oracle database instance is running NOARCHIVELOG mode
Goal:  perform ARCHIVE LOG CURRENT (in ARCHIVELOG mode) or LOGFILE SWITCH (in NOARCHIVELOG mode) in order to force a full database checkpoint, then put entire database into BACKUP mode

* Update WorkloadPatch.py

1) continue to call Oracle SQL*Plus with "-S" flag to suppress banners, prompts, etc
2) Call Oracle SQL*Plus with "-R 2" flag to restrict use of SQL*Plus access to underlying operating system.  For example, permit use of the START (or "@") command to run SQL scripts, but remove use of HOST or SPOOL commands
3) Change call to Oracle SQL*Plus from forcing connection to database when called, to instead starting program without forcing connection to database, using "/NOLOG" switch instead of database credentials.
NOTE:  the "preOracleMaster.sql" and "postOracleMaster.sql" scripts called by SQL*Plus will connect to the database as the limited SYSBACKUP role using external OS authentication instead of connecting to the database the all-powerful SYSDBA role using external authentication

Fix for Internal DNS Check I needed the ability to disable the internal DNS check, and while the public_setting is exposed, there is a bug where it was not being handled correctly and didn't work.  Setting a var to a string value makes it a 'true' boolean value when used for a boolean operation regardless of what the string value actually is.

This change uses the strtobool function to convert the string value that is optionally defined in public_settings ('enableInternalDNSCheck') into a true boolean value for the 'enable_idns_check' variable, so that the idns check is executes as expected.  Omitting 'enableInternalDNSCheck' from the public_settings results in a default of 'true' (as it was) while allowing a string value of 'y, yes, t, true, on or 1' for boolean true and a string value of 'n, no, f, false, off and 0' as a boolean false.

Log the patching result for the MDS Daemon on Linux Using SysLogHandler of the module Logging. (https://docs.python.org/2/library/logging.handlers.html#sysloghandler)
Log level is logging.INFO. It means only the messages whose level is higher than logging.INFO can be logged.
Using three types of message: info, warning and error. Their levels are all higher the logging.INFO.
Address is '/dev/log'. It means the messages will be logged into the syslog.
Message format is '%(name)s: %(levelname)s %(message)s'.

Provide status check of VM before and after patching 1. We provide a template script before and after the patching,
e.g. call "is_vm_idle" method before patching,
and "is_vm_healthy" method after patching. The two methods
return true by default. if "is_vm_idle" returns true, OSPatching
extension will continue. "is_vm_healthy" just reports the status,
it won't affect the execution.
2. The check results will be logged.
3. Admin can overwrite the script with their customized function.
4. Admin can also skip the check and kick off the patching.
5. Support the user defined script to be store locally,
from a storage account, or from external storage (e.g. github).
